<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

<p>JekyllBook is built on top of jekyll. Simply run</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gem install jekyll
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>to install jekyll, and serve it in the root directory of this repository with</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>jekyll -s --trace --baseurl ''
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>The table of contents / sidebar is located in the <code class="highlighter-rouge">_config.yml</code>.
Simply set up your config in this format:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>chapters:
  - path: chapters/01.md
    sections:
      - path: chapters/01-1.md
      - path: chapters/01-2.md
  - path: chapters/02.md
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Then, each of your chapters / sections should be prefaced with the Jekyll header:</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>---
layout: default
title: Name Of Chapter
---
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><a href="https://katex.org/">Katex</a> is supported out of the box, so you can write equations easily with</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">\begin{aligned}
i \hbar \frac{\partial}{\partial t}\Psi(\mathbf{r},t) = \hat H \Psi(\mathbf{r},t)
\end{aligned}</script>

